KnownLibraries.Name: ESP_EEPROM
KnownLibraries.Author: j-watson <j-watson@ntlworld.com>
KnownLibraries.Sentence: An improved EEPROM library for ESP8266
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: The ESP8266 family doesn't have genuine EEPROM memory so it is normally emulated by using a section of flash memory.  With the standard library, the sector needs to be re-flashed every time the changed EEPROM data needs to be saved.  For small amounts of EEPROM data this is very slow and will wear out the flash memory more quickly.  This library writes a new copy of your data when you save (commit) it and keeps track of where in the sector the most recent copy is kept.  The flash sector only needs to be erased when there is no more space for copies in the flash sector.  You can keep track of this yourself to do a time-consuming erase when most convenient or the library will do it for you when there is no more space for the data when you commit it.

KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Do multiple things at once, the straigt forward way. This is an alternative to the official Arduino Scheduler https://www.arduino.cc/en/reference/scheduler. Please share your experience with CopyThreads on github with me!

KnownLibraries.Name: Ticker
KnownLibraries.Author: Bert Melis
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows to call functions with a given interval.

KnownLibraries.Name: Stepper
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows Arduino boards to control a variety of stepper motors.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: This library allows you to control unipolar or bipolar stepper motors. To use it you will need a stepper motor, and the appropriate hardware to control it.

KnownLibraries.Name: ESP32httpUpdate
KnownLibraries.Author: Matej Sychra
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Http Update for ESP32
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Quick clone of Arduino ESP8266httpUpdate for ESP32 (without HTTPS requirement)

KnownLibraries.Name: RF24Network
KnownLibraries.Author: TMRh20
KnownLibraries.Sentence: OSI Layer 3 Networking for nrf24L01(+) devices.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Provides a simple and seamless network layer for sensor/IoT networks, including routing, addressing and fragmentation/reassembly.

KnownLibraries.Name: WiFiManager
KnownLibraries.Author: tzapu
KnownLibraries.Sentence: ESP8266 WiFi Connection manager with fallback web configuration portal
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Library for configuring ESP8266 modules WiFi credentials at runtime.

KnownLibraries.Name: ESPAsyncUDP-master
KnownLibraries.Author: Me-No-Dev
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Async UDP Library for ESP8266
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Async UDP Library for ESP8266

KnownLibraries.Name: LedControl
KnownLibraries.Author: Eberhard Fahle <e.fahle@wayoda.org>
KnownLibraries.Sentence: A library for the MAX7219 and the MAX7221 Led display drivers.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: The library supports multiple daisychained drivers and supports Led-Matrix displays as well as 7-Segment displays.

KnownLibraries.Name: Wire
KnownLibraries.Author: Hristo Gochkov
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows the communication between devices or sensors connected via Two Wire Interface Bus. For esp8266 boards.
